            <biogHist>
                <p>William Jolly was the son of David Jolly, tanner, and Mary Jolly n√©e Anderton and
                    while he was a teacher he married Mary Anne Thomson who was also a teacher. We
                    know they had at least one daughter, Mary Duncan. William died in 1915 and the
                    causes of death recorded were hemplegia, bronchitis and cardiac failure. William
                    Jolly was a representative of the new post-1872 order in Scottish education and
                    even though he had no Gaelic he was greatly enthusiastic about Carmichael's work
                    and the work of the Gaelic Society of Inverness. </p>
